name: HTMLLinkElement
description: The HTMLLinkElement interface represents reference information for external resources and the relationship of those resources to a document and vice-versa. This object inherits all of the properties and methods of the HTMLElement interface.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.as
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the type of content that is being loaded by the HTML link.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.charset
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the character encoding for the target resource.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.crossOrigin
members.description: Is a DOMString that corresponds to the CORS setting for this link element. See CORS settings attributes for details.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.disabled
members.description: Is a Boolean which represents whether the link is disabled; currently only used with style sheet links.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.href
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the URI for the target resource.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.hreflang
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the language code for the linked resource.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.media
members.description: Is a DOMString representing a list of one or more media formats to which the resource applies.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the referrerpolicy HTML attribute indicating which referrer to use.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.rel
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the forward relationship of the linked resource from the document to the resource.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.relList
members.description: Is a DOMTokenList that reflects the rel HTML attribute, as a list of tokens.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.rev
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the reverse relationship of the linked resource from the resource to the document.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.sizes
members.description: Is a DOMSettableTokenList that reflects the sizes HTML attribute, as a list of tokens.

members.name: LinkStyle.sheet
members.description: Returns the StyleSheet object associated with the given element, or null if there is none.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.target
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the name of the target frame to which the resource applies.

members.name: HTMLLinkElement.type
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the MIME type of the linked resource.
